<title>William Levi Dawson, African American Composer & Choral Director</title>
<meta name="keywords" content="African American Arranger, African American Comp, African American Professor, Choral Director, Negro Folk Symphony, Spirituals, Tuskegee Institute, William Levi Dawson">
<meta name="description" content="William Levi Dawson (1899-1990) was an African American composer and professor of Music who arranged spirituals for his choirs at Tuskegee Institute.  Dawson's &quot;Negro Folk Symp&#293;ony&quot; has been recorded by the Detroit Symphony Orchestra on Chandos 9226 (1993).">
